Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setPromotedMacroPin(25.10)                          setPromotedMacroPin(25.10)

Name
       setPromotedMacroPin  -  Selects or marks signal and/or PG pin shapes to
       be promoted later on

Syntax
        setPromotedMacroPin

       [-help]

       {-reset  | -reportOnlyFile <fileName.tcl> |

        {[-insts {<instName> | <instNameList>}]

         [-pins {<pinName> | <pinNameList>}]

         [-layers {<layerId> | <layerIdList>}]

         [-override ]

         [-abuttedToBoundaryOnly ]}}

       Selects or marks signal and/or PG pin shapes to be promoted  later  on.
       You can use this command before assigning pins.

       Note: The setPromotedMacroPin command should be called after specifying
       the  maximum and minimum metal layer names for promoting macro pins us-
       ing the setPinAssignMode -promotedMacroMaxLayer <maxLayer> and -promot-
       edMacroMinLayer <minLaye>r parameters, respectively.

Parameters
       -abuttedToBoundaryOnly
              Specifies that all macro pin shapes that are abutted to the par-
              tition boundary will be selected for promotion. The -pins  para-
              meter can also be used to select abutted pins .

              Note: You can use the -maxChannelWidthAsAbutted parameter of the
              setPinAssignMode  command  to enable thin channels in the design
              to be considered as abutted partitions  in  the  pin  assignment
              flow.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each setPromotedMacroPin  parameter. For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man setPromotedMacroPin

       -insts {<instName> | <instNameList>}
              Specifies the name of instances. You can also use wildcard (* or
              ?)  for  specifying  the  instance  names. This parameter is op-
              tional. If -insts is not specified, all BLOCK, PAD,  and  AREAIO
              macros  are selected.

              This is similar to specifying -insts *

              Data_type: string, optional

       -layers {<layerId> | <layerIdList>}
              Specifies  the  metal layer(s) of the macro pins. This parameter
              is optional. If -layers is not specified, all pin layers between
              setPinAssignMode  -promotedMacroMinLayer  and   setPinAssignMode
              -promotedMacroMaxLayer range are selected.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -override
              Specifies to override specific option(s) where previous settings
              of  these  options will be removed and be replaced by new speci-
              fied value(s). For example, specifying setPromotedMacroPin -lay-
              ers {} -override means no layer is promoted from now on.

              Note: All setPromotedMacroPin commands are incremental  with  no
              conflict resolution, unless the -override option is used.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pins {<pinName> | <pinNameList>}
              Specifies  the  name of macro pins. You can also use wildcard (*
              or ?) for specifying the pin names. This parameter is  optional.
              If  -insts  is  not  specified,  all signal and P/G pins are se-
              lected. This is similar to specifying -pins *

              Data_type: string, optional

       -reportOnlyFile <fileName.tcl>
              Writes out all setPromotedMacroPin settings in  memory  into  an
              output TCL file.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -reset Resets all or specified promoted pin selections.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
              * The  following command promotes the top most layer pins of se-
                lected macros

                setPinAssignMode  -promotedMacroMinLayer   4   -promotedMacro-
                MaxLayer 8

                setPromotedMacroPin -reset

                setPromotedMacroPin -insts {A B} -pins * -layers {7 8}

                setPromotedMacroPin -insts B -pins X -layers 8 -override

                setPromotedMacroPin -insts C -layers 5 -abuttedToBoundaryOnly

                setPromotedMacroPin -insts C -layers {8}

                setPromotedMacroPin -insts C -pins D[*] -layers {} -override

                setPromotedMacroPin -insts D -pins OUT

                setPromotedMacroPin -insts D -pins CLK -abuttedToBoundaryOnly

                assignIoPins

